---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="About gigcodelife.">
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-173 px-8 max-sm:px-5 pt-10 max-sm:pt-8 pb-16 max-sm:pb-12">
    <span class="text-eyebrow uppercase text-gray-500">About</span>
    <h1 class="text-h1 max-sm:text-h2 text-ink mt-4 mb-8">About gigcodelife</h1>
    <div class="text-body-lg text-ink">
      <p>
        gigcodelife is written by someone who spends part of the week driving gig
        platforms and the rest building software — including, sometimes, the kind
        of apps this site complains about. The gig economy has more going on under
        the hood than most drivers get told: pay guarantees nobody explains, app
        behavior nobody debugs, opportunities nobody flags. This is that layer,
        written in plain language, with real numbers instead of vibes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
